post_summaries.description: The Instagram post is a video of a woman speaking at a podium in front of a church congregation. The church logo "Friendship Church" is visible behind her. Text overlayed on the video reads "Psalm 23 The Lord Is!". The woman is wearing a black t-shirt with white writing. A chandelier hangs from the ceiling.
The image is a selfie of Whitteneylynn. She is wearing a black hoodie and a black baseball cap. The post is tagged with hashtags related to weight loss, health, and fitness.
The image shows a close-up of a red Tommy Hilfiger hoodie with what appears to be a Louis Vuitton patch on it. The caption mentions making hoodies all summer in preparation for the fall.
The image shows a black puppy (identified as a "corkie" or corkie puppy in the hashtags) lying on a small patch of artificial grass, presumably for potty training.

The image is a video post on Instagram showing a group of people, likely members of a fraternity or sorority, performing a synchronized dance routine. The caption and hashtags indicate involvement with Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Inc. (Nupe), Norfolk State University (#NSU), and Historically Black Colleges and Universities (#HBCU).
The image is a selfie of whitteneylynn holding a black puppy named Jukebox Jazz. The puppy has a blue dog tag with a phone number on it.
